commit.message:
Add armv6 and armv7 build and docker targets

Fixes: #12
Fix link to dockerhub

Fix errors trying to parse temperatures from switched off thermostat

FritzOS 7.29 and Comet DECT devices send the special state values in
Thermostat.Goal where ad FritzOS 7.31 and Fritz!DECT 301 devices send
the state in Thermostat.Saving.

Parsing has been fixed in https://github.com/jayme-github/fritzctl:
8f69fe815d3fdfbc9f36131fe5e29bad70645445

Don't try to parse goal, comfort or saving temparature if thermostat is
not in ON state.

Fixes: #11

Add listen address and version flag

Add new command line flags:
-listen-address=":9103"
-version

Also fix container build date to be the actual build date.
Add passwd to goreleaser extra_files

Add fritzbox_thermostat_state metric

This adds a new metric fritzbox_thermostat_state representing the
thermostat state: 1/0 (on/off), -1 if unknown or error.
As the termostat state is privided via special values of the thermstats
goal temperature, the goal temperature can not be read if the termostate
is in off state (e.g. the metric will not show up/will not be updated in
that case).
Also fix a couple of error messages in case optional values could not be
read from thermostats.

Fixes #10

Allow to configure fritzctl log level (default to "warn" now)

The default log level used to be "info" which seems unnecessary high and
leads to "Login sucessfull" messages all over the place. This change
sets the default level to "warn", adding a flag to make it configurable.
Make exporter run as non-root

Skip parsing of not present devices

Devices which are not present do not return valid (last) data in all
cases. As there is no real use in parsing them (last valid data has most
likely been scraped already anyways when the device was last present),
skip parsing of not present devices.
Update metrics in README

Add generic battery metrics

At some point, AVM exposed generic battery metrics (not just in the hkr
elements for thermostats). This change adds two new metrics for devices
running on battery power:
* fritzbox_battery_charge_level
* fritzbox_batterylow

The thermostat specific battery metrics
`fritzbox_thermostat_battery_charge_level` and
`fritzbox_thermostat_batterylow` will be kept around, but should be
considered deprecated.

Add metric for humidity sensors

This adds support for humidity sensors (as available in Fritz DECT 440
devices), exporting a new gauge metric: fritzbox_humidity_percent

Fixes #9

Retry fetching the Devicelist once on error

This is useful when FritzOS decides to log out all users from a specific
IP because of "abuse". Logging in again will be possible right away, so
there is no need to return an error in that case.

Add more metrics from thermostats

* fritzbox_thermostat_battery_charge_level
* fritzbox_thermostat_comfort
* fritzbox_thermostat_goal
* fritzbox_thermostat_saving
* fritzbox_thermostat_window_open
Update fritzctl to archived master version
Fix version for docker image tags and license

Return invalid metrics on parser errors

Generalize switch metrics and return invalid metrics in case of any
parser error.
Add new metrics to README

Add metrics for thermostat error and battery stats

This adds two new metrics for thermostats:
fritzbox_thermostat_batterylow: 0 if the battery is OK, 1 if it
is running low on capacity (this seems to be very unreliable)
fritzbox_thermostat_errorcode: Thermostat error code (0 = OK),
see https://avm.de/fileadmin/user_upload/Global/Service/Schnittstellen/AHA-HTTP-Interface.pdf
Update gopkg.in/yaml.v2 to v2.4.0

Migrate from travis to github actions

Use goreleaser for build and release of binaries and docker images.

Update to go 1.17

Fix windows build:
upgraded golang.org/x/sys v0.0.0-20200420163511-1957bb5e6d1f =>
 v0.0.0-20211216021012-1d35b9e2eb4e
Skip cleanup for docker build(x) as well
Build multi-arch docker images

Build for arm and arm64 as well

Fixes #7

Make the collector return an error if unable to fetch device list

The collector returned HTTP 200 even in case it occurred while fetching
device stats from the box.

Don't try to parse temperature and power data for absent devices

Absent devices don't provide temperature and power date which results in
parsing errors in stringToFloatMetric. As API knows about the absence
of a device, reading temperature and power data can easily be skipped.

This commit also adds a test case for the collector that would have
catched this issue.

Fixes: #4

Deprecate FRITZBOX_USER and FRITZBOX_PASSWORD

...in favor of USERNAME and PASSWORD to align with the other flags.
FRITZBOX_USER and FRITZBOX_PASSWORD will still be used, but a message
will be printed, asking to migate away from them.
Actually link to docker hub
